{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place pine nuts in mixing bowl and toast <b>5 min\/Varoma\/\/speed <b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside to cool.","Place Parmesan and parsley in mixing bowl then chop <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to bowl with toasted pine nuts and set aside.","Place onion, butternut squash and oil in mixing bowl then chop <b>10 sec\/speed 4.5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then sauté <b>4 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add wine followed by rice and sage leaves then, without measuring cup, cook <b>2 min\/120°C\/\/speed 1<b>. Scrape bottom of mixing bowl well with spatula to loosen rice.","Add stock, salt and pepper then cook <b>10 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>.","Add chicken and heat <b>5 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>.","Add reserved parsley-Parmesan mixture and butter, then stir in with spatula. Taste risotto and adjust seasoning if desired, then leave to rest for 2 minutes. Serve immediately with the toasted pine nuts scattered over the top."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["50 g pine nuts","40 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces (2 cm)","20 g fresh parsley","60 g onion, halved","300 g butternut squash, peeled, cut in pieces (2 cm)","20 g olive oil","150 g dry white wine","250 g risotto rice","10 - 12 fresh sage leaves","600 g chicken stock","1 ½ tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground black pepper, or more to taste","200 g cooked chicken meat, cut in pieces (2 cm)","20 g unsalted butter"]}],"id":"r75703","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-zFX_IhbvMHo\/XZQHwo1SsdI\/AAAAAAAAcL0\/8Xy-nG0FAaUmI7IbraHp68o5bleDihZFQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_qOV5XHxk2dSv35_0.png","title":"Chicken, Butternut Squash and Toasted Pine Nut Risotto","publishedAt":"2015-05-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"27.4 g","fat":"23.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"59.5 g","calories":"2326 kJ \/ 556 kcal"},"basicInfo":["easy","20m","45m","4 portions"]}